    <name>
      <text>Finding inverse of a function g(x)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>If \(g(x)={@const_1@}+{@coeff_x*x@}+e^x\), find \(g^{-1}({@const_1+1@})\)</p>
<p> \(g^{-1}({@const_1+1@})=\) [[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>In this case we cannot find \( g^{-1}(x), \) however we can use some elements of the domain of \(g\) to give us the image \({@const_1+1@},\) </p>
<p>\(g(-2)={@const_1@}+{@coeff_x@}(-2)+e^{-2}={@const_1+coeff_x*(-2)@}+\frac{1}{e^{2}}\)</p>
<p>\(g(-1)={@const_1@}+{@coeff_x@}(-1)+e^{-1}={@const_1+coeff_x*(-1)@}+\frac{1}{e}\)</p>
<p>\(g(0)={@const_1@}+0+e^0={@const_1+coeff_x*(0)@}+1={@const_1+1@}\)</p>
<p>Thus, \(g^{-1}({@const_1+1@})=0.\)</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
